# TOP — directory-scoped ownership
#
# Per ADR-0015. Every directory in the repository has an owner.
# Pull requests modifying files in a directory require approval from at
# least one of that directory's owners. Cross-cutting changes (touching
# Core + one or more workflow extensions) require approval from each
# affected owner.
#
# Today the convener (@bo-lora) is the only steward; every owner entry
# resolves to that GitHub user. As working groups form, the relevant
# directory's owner is reassigned to the GitHub team representing that
# working group (e.g., `@scientixai/clinical-research-wg`). The history
# of who owned what is queryable through git blame on this file.

# === Default owner (catch-all) ===

*                                       @bo-lora


# === Project-level documents ===

/README.md                              @bo-lora
/CONTRIBUTING.md                        @bo-lora
/LICENSE                                @bo-lora
